Package syntax

Class Term

java.lang.Object
syntax.Term
Direct Known Subclasses:
ConstantTerm, FunctionalSymbolTerm, VariableTerm
public abstract class Term extends Object
A node of first-order term syntax tree. It is identified by its name and type.

    • fromString

      public static Term fromString(@NotNull @NotNull String termString)
      Creates a syntax tree of first-order term from string input.

      Valid terms may have one of the following forms:
      c<index> - constant
      x<index> - variable
      f<index>( <term>,<term>...<term> ) - term with functional symbol of arity > 0

      Parser uses recursive descent algorithm to process tokens.

      Parameters:
      termString - sequence of tokens representing first-order term
      Returns:
      syntax tree of provided first-order term
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if term is of invalid form
      NullPointerException - if termString is null

    • getDomain

      public abstract Set<String> getDomain()
      Returns a set of variables that are present in this term. Every variable in the domain is represented as string. Returned set is empty If term contains no variables. Note that returned set is immutable.
      Returns:
      immutable set of variables
